    },
    {
      "id": "1436285990586159174",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2025-11-07T09:27:45.059+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "As an end goal, that seems fine, but when things are getting started, I wouldn't rush.\nBeside the obvious \"does it work\" and \"demo effect\" :\n(1) being the first run, there is also the question of how packaging / bonding will work out which might influence what people want to do for the next runs.\n(2) I don't have the numbers, but I would expect the first few runs might end up being run at a loss and it might take time for people to get moving designing stuff, so not burning all capital before that happens would be good \ud83d\ude05",
      "author": {
        "id": "596068704471482370",
        "name": "246tnt",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "tnt",
        "color": null,
        "isBot": false,
        "roles": [],
